address: 20-1 Yeongtong-dong, Yeongtong-gu, Suwon-si, Gyeonggi-do, South Korea

description: The Myeongdong Art Theater is located in Seoul, South Korea. It was built in the 1830s and is an art performance venue with a long history. From 1934 to 1973, the Old Myeongdong Theater played the role of a pioneer in Korean culture and art, such as a movie hall, a performance hall, and an art theater. In addition, the night view of the theater is very beautiful.

Ewhajang, located in Jongno-gu, Seoul, is a Joseon Dynasty building. There were many pear trees on the hills of Naksan in the Joseon Dynasty, and it was named after the name of the pavilion at that time.
